      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SWEET STRIKE (9) has had a couple of months off but was racing consistently before that let-up, coming from this barrier for third here last start. Kept up to the mark with a trial and has strong winning claims with manners as does LUV THE NITELIFE (10) who took advantage of the ace draw to find winning form at her most recent outing, leading to score at Penrith by 3 metres. Interesting to see what unfolds from this wide draw but was runner-up in two of her other three starts here since a long spell. Could go on with it now that she is back in winning form. MCWIZARD (7) draws wider but did a good job for third when resuming at this circuit and distance last time out and should be fitter. YA RACIN ARLO (1) has been producing some decent efforts and gets the aid of the ace draw.",
